data.title: Grand Duchess Olga Alexandrovna of Russia
data.meta_description:
Grand Duchess Olga Alexandrovna of Russia - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. 1) Grand Duchess Olga Alexandrovna of Russia was the youngest child of Emperor Alexander III of Russia and sister of Emperor Nicholas II. 

2) She was raised outside St. Petersburg but had a distant relationship with her mother and was close with her father, who died when she was 12. 

3) She had two marriages, the first was unconsummated and annulled, the second was to a cavalry officer with whom she had two sons. She fled revolutionary Russia with her second husband and family in 1920.
